RACE.FOOTNOTES: SURPLUS got put in tight early, chased outside rivals early, bid three deep nearing the turn, fought three wide into the stretch, dueled outside the runner-up through the lane and got up. BOB'S SNIPER set the pace and crossed over early, got pressured nearing the turn, held a short lead through the turn along the inside, dueled with SURPLUS down the stretch and got nailed at the wire. RESTLESS RAMBLER forwardly placed off the inside, bid between foes leaving the backstretch, lost touch with the top pair late on the bend and stayed on to secure the show. SHARP WARNING had to steady between rivals early, came four wide into the lane and summoned a mild response. TIME IS GONE chased along the inside into the turn, moved off the rail around the bend and failed to rally. STREET BEHAVIOR got shuffled between foes early, asked two wide into the bend and lacked the needed response. JAY BOY broke well but lacked early speed and dropped back, got bumped four wide entering the turn, spun three wide into the lane and failed to menace. RUN KING STUD RUN dropped back early, raced three deep then got bumped and put in tight entering the turn, angled down to the rail around the bend and was not a factor.
